      "content": "Do **not** take more insulin, as the symptoms you are experiencing (shakiness, sweating, confusion) are classic signs of dangerous hypoglycemia (low blood sugar), which can worsen with additional insulin. You should immediately check your blood glucose level with a meter to confirm the cause and treat it with fast-acting carbohydrates like juice or glucose tablets. If your confusion gets worse or you do not feel better quickly, please seek emergency medical help right away.",
